  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Quality Education Programme in the DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Many rural primary schools in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) are very poorly equipped and run, resulting in high drop-out rates for children, and poor results in examinations. Parental involvement is minimal, and Government priorities lie elsewhere. This project aims to increase the numbers of rural children in Southern DRC who go to and learn in school. It works to make these improvements sustainable by promoting effective teaching and learning, and by getting children, teachers, parents and their communities to participate meaningfully in developing and implementing school improvement plans. Special attention is paid to keeping girls in school and making schools accessible for disabled and minority pupils..</narrative>
  </description>
